reviews.text: Gone downhill in recent years. Used to be a good menu but now it’s literally cheese, seafood and beef. Actually didn’t order anything for myself today, nothing appealing. I’ll eat elsewhere after. Not worth the price and no longer a family eatery.
The food is tasty and visually appealing too. The waiters are nice. However, this restaurant is expensive. You can get a whole day's worth of fast food from the price of 1 meal here.

Ruby Tuesday has a clever membership plan where almost no one would refuse, because you pay half price with it. I almost never see a patron without a membership. Food is good, though. The steak is almost a must try, so are the snacks and finger food.
A great place to have some classically western fare, but the prices are very steep unless you have invested in a member card.
